libxcb
------------------------------------------
libxcb provides an interface to the X Window System protocol, which replaces
the current Xlib interface. It has several advantages over Xlib, including:
- size: small library and lower memory footprint
- latency hiding: batch several requests and wait for the replies later
- direct protocol access: one-to-one mapping between interface and protocol
- proven thread support: transparently access XCB from multiple threads
- easy extension implementation: interfaces auto-generated from XML-XCB

Xlib can also use XCB as a transport layer, allowing software to make
requests and receive responses with both, which eases porting to XCB.
However, client programs, libraries, and toolkits will gain the most
benefit from a native XCB port.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-50
  libgcc1-4.3.2-2
  libXau6-1.0.4-10
  libXdmcp6-1.0.2-10

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-10
  automake1.10-1.10.2-10
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.9.7-1
  gawk-3.1.6-2
  gcc4-core-4.3.2-2
  libpthread-stubs-0.1-1
  libxslt-1.1.24-10
  make-3.81-2
  pkg-config-0.23b-10
  python-2.5.4-10
  sed-4.1.5-2
  xcb-proto-1.5-1

Canonical website:
  http://xcb.freedesktop.org/

Canonical download:
  http://xcb.freedesktop.org/dist/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libxcb-1.2-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libxcb-1.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libxcb-1.2-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-composite-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-composite0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-damage-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-damage0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-doc-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-dpms-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-dpms0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-glx-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-glx0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-randr-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-randr1-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-record-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-record0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-render-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-render0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-res-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-res0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-screensaver-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-screensaver0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-shape-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-shape0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-shm-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-shm0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-sync-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-sync0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xfixes-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xfixes0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xinerama-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xinerama0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xinput-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xinput0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xtest-devel-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xtest0-1.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb1-1.2-X.tar.bz2

Or use 'cygport libxcb-1.2-X.cygport prep' to get a patched 
source directory.

To find out the files included in each binary package, you can
use "cygcheck -l <PKG>".

